<%#
  views/partials/offline-banner.ejs

  What:  App-wide "you're offline" strip. Hidden by default; /js/app.js
         (bindOfflineIndicator) reveals it when the browser fires the
         `offline` event and hides it again on `online`. Complements the
         service-worker offline.html fallback (which only covers full-page
         navigations) by giving live, in-app feedback when the connection
         drops mid-session — so the user sees a friendly message instead of
         silently-failing actions.
  Why:   The app is used as a web-app on mobile; a dropped signal must read
         as "you're offline", not a broken page (per the user).
  Used:  Included once from views/_layout.ejs (renders in every mode).
-%>
<div id="offline-banner" class="offline-banner" role="status" aria-live="polite" hidden>
    <span class="offline-banner__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
    <span class="offline-banner__text">You’re offline — some features won’t work until you reconnect.</span>
</div>
